# YAML Data Files Guidelines

When editing YAML data files in the `_data/` directory:

## Structure Requirements
- **Authors**: Use the format defined in [_data/authors.yml](mdc:_data/authors.yml) with `first_name`, `last_name`, `website`, and `is_me` fields
- **Publications**: Follow the schema in [_data/publications.yml](mdc:_data/publications.yml) with required fields like `title`, `venue`, `authors`, and optional fields like `paper`, `arxiv`, `video`, etc.
- **Projects**: Use the format from [_data/projects.yml](mdc:_data/projects.yml) with `title`, `venue`, `description`, and optional `webpage` links

## Content Guidelines
- Always maintain consistent author references using the keys from [_data/authors.yml](mdc:_data/authors.yml)
- Include proper venue formatting (conference/journal name, year)
- Add descriptions that are informative but concise
- Use markdown formatting in description fields when needed
- Include all relevant links (paper, video, GitHub, project page, etc.)

## Image References
- Images should be stored in `images/` with publication-specific subdirectories
- Use relative paths like `publications/project_name/image.jpg`
- Provide both static images and optional mouseover videos/images
- Ensure images are 1:1 aspect ratio, minimum 320px

## Common Fields
- `title`: Publication/project title
- `venue`: Conference, journal, or context
- `authors`: List of author keys from authors.yml
- `description`: Detailed description (supports markdown)
- `image`: Path to preview image
- `paper`: Direct link to paper PDF
- `arxiv`: ArXiv ID (just the ID, not full URL)
- `video`: Link to video demonstration
- `webpage`: Link to project page or GitHub
- `awards`: Special recognition or awards
